WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.120
The Jungle Book by Rudyard Kipling Copyright Blackcat Publishing

00:15.120 --> 00:25.360
Chapter 1 Mughli's Family One evening in the hills of South India,

00:25.360 --> 00:31.920
Father Wolf wakes up. Mother Wolf is near him with four little cubs.

00:32.880 --> 00:40.480
It's time to look for food. Says Father Wolf. He gets up and leaves the cave.

00:41.680 --> 00:47.760
There is a big moon in the sky. Hello. Says a voice.

00:47.760 --> 00:56.640
It is the jackal, Tabakwe. He eats everything, even old clothes from the villages.

00:57.840 --> 01:03.920
The wolves do not like him and are afraid of him. What do you want, Tabakwe?

01:04.880 --> 01:11.840
asks Father Wolf. The tiger, Sheer Khan, is coming here to look for food.

01:12.720 --> 01:14.560
Says Tabakwe. What?

01:15.920 --> 01:24.000
Says Father Wolf surprised. He can't do that. He must tell us first because that's the law of

01:24.000 --> 01:32.880
the jungle. Sheer Khan has a bad leg and he can't run fast. Says Mother Wolf.

01:33.040 --> 01:43.120
He only kills bulls and the people of the village are angry with him. That's why he's coming here.

01:43.920 --> 01:46.880
He wants to start hunting in a new place.

01:48.320 --> 01:53.840
Listen. Says Tabakwe. You can hear him in the woods.

01:54.640 --> 02:04.720
Father Wolf listens and says. What a stupid animal. He's making a lot of noise and all the animals

02:04.720 --> 02:10.400
are going to run away and hide. How can I look for food now?

02:11.040 --> 02:18.880
Shh. Says Mother Wolf. It's the noise of a man.

02:18.880 --> 02:30.240
A man? Cries Father Wolf. The law of the jungle says that animals must not eat man

02:30.880 --> 02:38.000
because then a lot of men with guns come to the jungle and all of the animals are in danger.

02:38.960 --> 02:45.680
Listen. Says Mother Wolf. Something's coming to the cave.

02:47.520 --> 02:56.080
Father Wolf sees a baby standing under a tree. The baby looks at Father Wolf and laughs.

02:58.080 --> 03:07.040
Is that a man cub? asks Mother Wolf. Bring it here. I want to look at it.

03:08.080 --> 03:17.600
The baby is small and has no clothes. Father Wolf gently carries it to Mother Wolf.

03:18.880 --> 03:25.760
It starts drinking her milk with the other cubs. Mother Wolf is happy and says.

03:27.120 --> 03:32.480
Look. He's drinking my milk with the cubs. He's not afraid.

03:32.640 --> 03:40.160
It is suddenly dark in the cave because Sheer Khan puts his big head inside.

03:40.160 --> 03:49.680
We're pleased to see you, Sheer Khan. Says Father Wolf. But his eyes are angry.

03:49.680 --> 03:57.520
I know. There's a man cub here. Says Sheer Khan.

03:57.760 --> 04:10.640
It's mine. You must give it to me. Sheer Khan's very big so he can't come into the cave.

04:11.280 --> 04:17.760
thinks Father Wolf. The man cub is ours. Says Father Wolf.

04:19.120 --> 04:25.280
The leader of the pack's going to decide what to do with the cub. We listen to him,

04:25.280 --> 04:30.720
and not to a tiger. The man cub is mine.

04:31.680 --> 04:36.080
cries Sheer Khan angrily. He starts roaring.

04:38.320 --> 04:49.040
No! cries Mother Wolf. The man cub is mine and you can't kill him. He's going to live with us.

04:49.120 --> 04:59.120
He's my son. Now go away. Sheer Khan walks around the cave slowly and looks at the man cub.

05:00.320 --> 05:07.120
No. I'm Sheer Khan. And the cub is mine.

05:08.240 --> 05:17.840
You're wrong, says Mother Wolf. The man cub is ours. He's going to live with us. He's my son.

05:18.800 --> 05:28.080
Now go away, Sheer Khan. Father Wolf is surprised, but he knows Mother Wolf is brave and strong.

05:29.440 --> 05:35.200
Sheer Khan goes away. He knows he cannot fight Mother Wolf in the cave.

05:36.720 --> 05:46.880
One day, I'm going to have that cub. He cries. After Sheer Khan leaves, Father Wolf says,

05:47.920 --> 05:54.560
Do you really want to keep him? Yes, I do, says Mother Wolf.

05:56.480 --> 06:04.720
He isn't afraid of us, and he's happy here. I want to call him Mowgli the Frog.

06:05.680 --> 06:15.120
Mowgli, says Father Wolf. Yes, I like the name Mowgli. We must show Mowgli to the pack.

06:15.120 --> 06:23.200
The law of the jungle says that the pack must see all of the wolf cubs when they can walk,

06:23.840 --> 06:25.600
and look at them carefully.

06:30.320 --> 06:31.520
Listening activity.

06:33.680 --> 06:44.240
My name is Baloo. I'm a big bear, and I live in the jungle with baguera and the walms.

06:45.520 --> 06:54.000
I teach the cubs in the wolf pack about the law of the jungle. I know all the animals in the

06:54.000 --> 07:05.040
jungle. I am their friend, and I can speak their language. They know I don't hunt. I only eat

07:05.120 --> 07:16.160
nuts and honey. I'm baguera. I'm a black panther. I'm very strong.

07:18.080 --> 07:27.600
All the other animals say, I'm clever. They often ask me about things and ask me to help them.

07:28.480 --> 07:38.000
I'm going to help Baloo teach Mowgli, the man cub. I know about men, and I know they are clever too.

07:39.440 --> 07:47.840
I hope I can teach him everything he needs to know to live in the jungle. It's a difficult place to live.

07:47.840 --> 07:55.600
Chapter 2. Council Rock.

07:58.000 --> 08:05.200
When the four wolf cubs can walk, father wolf takes them and Mowgli to council rock.

08:06.640 --> 08:15.440
Mother wolf goes too. Hundreds of wolves in the wolf pack meet at council rock once a month

08:15.520 --> 08:24.000
when the moon is full. Akela is the leader of the pack and he sits on a big rock.

08:25.440 --> 08:35.520
He is a grey wolf and he is very brave. Each new wolf cub stands in front of him and he says,

08:36.480 --> 08:48.320
look carefully wolves. Look carefully. At last, father wolf pushes Mowgli in front of Akela and the other wolves.

08:49.920 --> 08:57.040
This is Mowgli the frog. Says father wolf. Mowgli just laughs.

08:57.200 --> 09:03.600
Suddenly, the wolves here shear Khan's voice behind the trees.

09:04.400 --> 09:14.960
The man cub is mine. Give him to me. He cries. Akela does not move but says,

09:15.920 --> 09:24.240
look carefully. Who speaks for this man cub? Two voices must speak for him,

09:24.880 --> 09:34.240
but not his father and mother. A big sleepy brown bear appears in front of Akela.

09:35.520 --> 09:44.080
Baloo says Akela surprised. Baloo teaches the law of the jungle to the wolf cubs

09:44.720 --> 09:52.480
and he speaks at the meetings of the council. Everyone likes him because he eats only nuts and

09:52.560 --> 10:01.520
honey. He doesn't hunt. I can speak for the man cub. Says Baloo with his low voice.

10:02.560 --> 10:15.200
I can teach him to run with the pack. Very well. Says Akela. Another animal silently jumps down

10:15.280 --> 10:24.080
into the circle of wolves. It is Bagira the panther. He is black, brave and strong.

10:24.880 --> 10:34.160
He is also very clever. Akela, can I speak? asks Bagira softly.

10:35.120 --> 10:44.000
Yes, you can. Says Akela. The law of the jungle says it's possible to buy

10:44.640 --> 10:54.640
the life of a cub. Says Bagira. It's bad to kill a man cub because he can't hurt you.

10:56.000 --> 11:06.880
Let him live and I can give you a fat bull to eat. Good, good. Say the young wolves.

11:07.520 --> 11:18.960
They are always hungry and want to eat the fat bull. Let him live. Very well. Says Akela.

11:20.960 --> 11:31.920
Look carefully, wolves. Look carefully. The wolves walk near Mowgli and look at him carefully.

11:32.720 --> 11:43.440
Then they go away and only Akela, Baloo, Bagira and Mowgli's wolf family are at the council.

11:44.880 --> 11:54.960
They can hear sheer calm roaring in the night. Men and their cubs are clever. Says Akela.

11:55.920 --> 12:05.920
One day this man cub can help us. Now take him away and teach him everything he must know.

12:08.160 --> 12:17.920
Thanks to Baloo's good words and Bagira's fat bull, Mowgli now belongs to the Cioni wolf pack.

12:18.080 --> 12:27.520
He grows up in the wolf family and he learns the songs of the birds and the sounds of the animals in the jungle.

12:27.520 --> 12:39.440
Baloo and Bagira are very good teachers. He learns to climb trees, swim in the river and hunt for his food.

12:40.240 --> 12:42.560
He is a happy boy.

12:47.360 --> 12:51.040
Chapter 3 Lessons with Baloo

12:53.600 --> 13:01.840
Mowgli is now around 10 years old. Baloo and Bagira love him and they are good teachers.

13:02.800 --> 13:09.200
Baloo likes teaching Mowgli because he is a good student and learns quickly.

13:10.960 --> 13:16.560
First he teaches him to hunt only when he is hungry and not for fun.

13:18.240 --> 13:25.760
Then he teaches him to speak to the different jungle people and he teaches him the important

13:25.760 --> 13:31.600
master words. Sometimes Mowgli gets tired of these lessons.

13:33.120 --> 13:38.160
One day he is not listening to his lesson and Baloo gets angry.

13:39.680 --> 13:45.840
He hits Mowgli gently on the head and the little boy runs away and climbs a tree.

13:46.800 --> 13:58.880
Baloo, don't hit little Mowgli, says Bagira. He is young. How can his little head remember all those long words?

14:00.400 --> 14:10.000
Those long words keep him safe from all the birds, snakes and other animals in the jungle.

14:10.640 --> 14:11.360
Says Baloo.

14:12.720 --> 14:23.600
I know he is young but the jungle is big and not always safe. There are dangers everywhere.

14:25.440 --> 14:34.720
Then he turns around and calls Mowgli. Mowgli, come and say the master words again.

14:35.040 --> 14:41.280
Mowgli climbs down the tree and goes to sit with Baloo and Bagira.

14:42.240 --> 14:48.880
I am going to say the words to Bagira, not to you, old Baloo.

14:48.880 --> 14:53.360
Says Mowgli. I know all the words.

14:53.360 --> 14:54.960
All right.

14:54.960 --> 14:56.800
Says Baloo.

14:56.800 --> 15:02.800
Say the words for the hunting people.

15:03.040 --> 15:08.400
We are of one blood, you and I.

15:09.280 --> 15:10.080
Says Mowgli.

15:10.960 --> 15:17.200
Good. Now say the words for the birds.

15:18.080 --> 15:24.400
Says Baloo. Mowgli says the same words but with the sound of a bird.

15:25.680 --> 15:29.760
And now for the snake people.

15:30.560 --> 15:31.280
Says Baloo.

15:32.880 --> 15:39.760
Mowgli says the same words but with the long sound of a snake.

15:40.960 --> 15:42.560
Very good.

15:42.560 --> 15:44.240
Says Baloo happily.

15:45.040 --> 15:53.520
With these words you are safe in the jungle because no bird, snake or animal can hurt you.

15:55.200 --> 15:59.120
Now I want to go up in the trees with my people.

16:00.000 --> 16:01.600
Says Mowgli happily.

16:02.560 --> 16:02.880
What?

16:03.600 --> 16:04.400
Says Baloo.

16:05.440 --> 16:07.600
Do you know the monkey people?

16:09.120 --> 16:12.240
Suddenly Baloo and Bagira are angry.

16:13.520 --> 16:16.160
Yes, I know the monkey people.

16:17.040 --> 16:18.000
Says Mowgli.

16:18.800 --> 16:23.520
They take me up in the trees and give me good things to eat.

16:24.480 --> 16:27.920
They're kind to me and call me brother.

16:28.880 --> 16:32.800
They play all day and don't do lessons.

16:34.080 --> 16:35.760
I like playing with them.

16:36.480 --> 16:37.360
Oh no.

16:38.080 --> 16:39.760
Says Baloo angrily.

16:40.560 --> 16:47.520
You know the law for all of the jungle people but the monkey people don't have a law.

16:48.320 --> 16:49.920
They don't have a leader.

16:50.880 --> 16:53.280
They're dirty and noisy.

16:54.240 --> 16:58.480
They talk all day and forget everything they say.

16:59.680 --> 17:02.880
The jungle people don't drink where the monkeys drink.

17:03.840 --> 17:07.360
We don't talk to them or think about them.

17:08.400 --> 17:11.280
Forget the monkey people, Mowgli.

17:12.000 --> 17:13.040
Says Bagira.

17:14.080 --> 17:19.040
They live in the trees and they throw nuts on our heads.

17:19.840 --> 17:21.040
Oh.

17:21.840 --> 17:23.440
Says Mowgli sadly.

17:24.640 --> 17:26.160
I'm very sorry.

17:28.160 --> 17:32.240
All this time the monkey people are sitting in the trees

17:32.880 --> 17:37.120
and they are listening to Baloo, Bagira and Mowgli.

17:38.640 --> 17:43.120
Suddenly they throw a lot of nuts and sticks on their heads.

17:43.920 --> 17:51.280
Baloo and Bagira take Mowgli away to another part of the jungle and they take a nap.

17:56.160 --> 17:57.360
Listening activity.

17:59.680 --> 18:04.800
First we are going to find some nuts for breakfast.

18:06.000 --> 18:11.280
Then you are going to learn all the master words.

18:12.080 --> 18:17.360
After we are going to get some bananas from the trees

18:18.240 --> 18:22.080
and I'm going to find some honey for us to eat.

18:23.520 --> 18:27.040
Bagira is going to find his own lunch.

18:28.720 --> 18:33.040
After lunch Bagira and I are going to sleep.

18:34.080 --> 18:40.160
Then in the afternoon you are going to hunt with Bagira.

18:42.160 --> 18:45.360
Chapter 4. Car.

18:48.160 --> 18:54.640
When Baloo and Bagira wake up after their nap, they can't find Mowgli.

18:56.000 --> 18:57.760
Where's Mowgli?

18:58.640 --> 18:59.840
Asks Bagira.

19:00.880 --> 19:04.640
Baloo looks up at a tree and sees Mowgli.

19:05.440 --> 19:08.880
The monkey people are holding his legs and arms.

19:09.440 --> 19:15.600
Baloo shouts angrily and Bagira tries to climb up the tree.

19:16.720 --> 19:19.520
But he is too heavy for the small branches.

19:20.880 --> 19:24.560
The monkeys laugh loudly and carry Mowgli away.

19:26.080 --> 19:29.280
Baloo and Bagira are very angry and worried.

19:30.560 --> 19:36.080
They follow the monkeys and Mowgli but the monkeys move very quickly.

19:36.160 --> 19:40.160
It is exciting for Mowgli to fly in the sky.

19:40.160 --> 19:44.000
The monkeys jump quickly from tree to tree.

19:44.000 --> 19:47.440
But Mowgli is afraid of falling.

19:47.440 --> 19:50.480
Where are the monkeys taking me?

19:50.480 --> 19:51.840
He thinks.

19:51.840 --> 19:54.800
I must tell Baloo and Bagira.

19:54.800 --> 19:56.400
But how?

19:56.400 --> 20:00.240
Suddenly he sees Ran.

20:00.240 --> 20:05.120
He is a big bird and he flies high in the blue sky.

20:05.920 --> 20:08.720
Ran sees the monkeys with a man-cup.

20:08.720 --> 20:13.360
He flies down and hears the master words of the birds.

20:13.360 --> 20:17.360
We are of one blood, you and I.

20:17.360 --> 20:20.480
You speak our language.

20:20.480 --> 20:22.000
Says Ran.

20:22.000 --> 20:23.920
Who are you?

20:23.920 --> 20:26.880
I'm Mowgli, the man-cup.

20:26.880 --> 20:28.560
Please help me.

20:28.560 --> 20:33.520
Find Baloo and Bagira and tell them about the birds.

20:34.000 --> 20:37.040
And tell them about the monkeys.

20:37.040 --> 20:38.320
All right.

20:38.320 --> 20:39.120
Says Ran.

20:40.400 --> 20:41.440
I can do that.

20:42.720 --> 20:43.920
And he flies away.

20:45.440 --> 20:51.120
The monkeys move quickly and soon Baloo and Bagira are far behind.

20:53.440 --> 20:55.440
We're too slow.

20:56.240 --> 20:57.040
Says Baloo.

20:58.000 --> 21:00.320
We can't follow the monkeys.

21:01.120 --> 21:02.640
Poor Mowgli.

21:02.640 --> 21:04.720
He is in danger.

21:04.720 --> 21:06.640
Poor Mowgli.

21:06.640 --> 21:08.080
Says Bagira.

21:08.080 --> 21:10.720
Oh, this is terrible.

21:10.720 --> 21:14.240
His big green eyes are sad.

21:14.240 --> 21:16.640
I have an idea.

21:16.640 --> 21:21.680
Where's Carr, the giant python?

21:21.680 --> 21:26.080
He climbs up trees quickly and easily.

21:26.080 --> 21:28.880
And he eats monkeys.

21:29.840 --> 21:31.760
Perhaps he can help us.

21:33.440 --> 21:35.680
Our clever idea, Bagira.

21:36.400 --> 21:37.280
Says Baloo.

21:38.240 --> 21:39.440
Let's look for him.

21:41.120 --> 21:43.680
They find Carr lying in the sun.

21:44.880 --> 21:48.080
He is a beautiful yellow and brown snake.

21:48.880 --> 21:51.120
And he is 10 meters long.

21:52.240 --> 21:55.840
He is very strong and very dangerous.

21:56.320 --> 21:57.840
Hello.

21:57.840 --> 22:00.880
Says Carr when he sees them.

22:00.880 --> 22:02.800
Hello, Carr.

22:02.800 --> 22:04.640
Says Baloo.

22:04.640 --> 22:06.720
We're looking for food.

22:06.720 --> 22:11.600
Oh, I'm very hungry.

22:11.600 --> 22:13.600
Says Carr.

22:13.600 --> 22:17.600
Let me come with you.

22:17.600 --> 22:20.800
We're following the monkey people.

22:20.800 --> 22:22.800
Says Baloo.

22:22.800 --> 22:27.120
They have our man cub and we want to find him.

22:27.120 --> 22:32.160
Why are you following the monkey people?

22:32.160 --> 22:34.240
Asks Carr.

22:34.240 --> 22:39.200
They took our man cub and we're angry.

22:39.200 --> 22:40.880
Says Baloo.

22:40.880 --> 22:44.640
We must find him now.

22:44.640 --> 22:46.640
Says Bagira.

22:47.280 --> 22:50.720
Carr looks interested and says,

22:50.720 --> 22:53.440
your man cub?

22:53.440 --> 22:54.960
Yes.

22:54.960 --> 22:56.560
Says Baloo.

22:56.560 --> 23:00.000
Our man cub, Mowgli.

23:00.000 --> 23:04.000
Bagira is very clever and says,

23:04.000 --> 23:09.840
the monkey people always call you bad names.

23:09.840 --> 23:13.840
They say you're an old young man.

23:14.400 --> 23:18.240
They say you're an old yellow worm.

23:21.600 --> 23:24.000
Says Carr angrily.

23:24.000 --> 23:31.760
Those noisy dirty monkeys must not call me bad names.

23:33.600 --> 23:34.800
Where are they?

23:36.080 --> 23:39.040
And where is your man cub?

23:40.800 --> 23:43.440
Suddenly they hear a voice from the sky.

23:44.480 --> 23:45.840
Look up Baloo.

23:46.720 --> 23:47.680
Shouts ran.

23:49.120 --> 23:50.080
Hello, Ran.

23:50.720 --> 23:51.600
Shouts Baloo.

23:52.800 --> 23:55.840
Mowgli's with the monkey people.

23:56.640 --> 23:57.600
Cries Ran.

23:58.400 --> 24:00.240
He's in the monkey city.

24:00.960 --> 24:02.160
The lost city.

24:04.160 --> 24:05.760
Mowgli's clever.

24:05.760 --> 24:07.840
He knows the master words.

24:09.200 --> 24:09.840
Good luck.

24:10.800 --> 24:12.800
The lost city?

24:12.800 --> 24:14.560
Says Bagira.

24:14.560 --> 24:15.520
Surprised.

24:16.160 --> 24:18.480
It's a very old city.

24:18.480 --> 24:20.800
And no one lives there.

24:20.800 --> 24:22.240
Yes.

24:22.240 --> 24:23.680
Says Baloo.

24:23.680 --> 24:26.720
Only the monkey people go there.

24:27.680 --> 24:31.920
We must leave immediately because it's far away.

24:32.640 --> 24:36.400
You move quickly, but I'm slow.

24:36.400 --> 24:38.400
I can follow you.

24:38.400 --> 24:39.280
I can follow you.

24:40.400 --> 24:40.720
Yes.

24:41.760 --> 24:42.960
Let's go.

24:44.080 --> 24:45.360
Says Carr.

24:45.360 --> 24:47.920
I'm very hungry.

24:48.960 --> 24:56.560
Those noisy monkeys can't call me an old yellow worm.

24:57.520 --> 25:01.520
I'm going to teach them something.

25:01.520 --> 25:08.240
Listening activity.

25:10.480 --> 25:10.800
One.

25:12.480 --> 25:14.000
What can you do, Ran?

25:14.880 --> 25:17.600
I can fly high in the sky.

25:18.560 --> 25:21.440
And I can sing to everyone below.

25:24.080 --> 25:24.320
Two.

25:25.760 --> 25:27.520
What can you do, Bagira?

25:28.400 --> 25:31.520
I'm a clever and silent hunter.

25:32.560 --> 25:35.120
I can jump long distances.

25:37.520 --> 25:37.920
Three.

25:39.360 --> 25:40.880
What can you do, Carr?

25:42.640 --> 25:44.240
I can dance.

25:45.280 --> 25:48.640
All the animals that see me dance.

25:49.440 --> 25:54.800
Want to walk towards me and fall into my mouth.

25:55.760 --> 25:57.120
Incredible.

26:02.560 --> 26:03.120
Four.

26:04.160 --> 26:06.400
What can you do, shear Carr?

26:11.280 --> 26:14.160
Everyone is scared of me.

26:15.600 --> 26:20.560
Men can't escape me because I can run very fast.

26:21.520 --> 26:24.880
And I can swim well too.

26:27.680 --> 26:28.240
Five.

26:29.440 --> 26:30.960
What can you do, Baloo?

26:32.960 --> 26:39.280
I can speak all the languages of the other animals in the jungle.

26:44.080 --> 26:45.120
Chapter Five.

26:45.920 --> 26:47.040
The Lost City.

26:47.520 --> 26:51.440
Everything in the Lost City is very old.

26:52.000 --> 26:58.240
There is a big palace on a hill and a water fountain near the King's Garden.

26:59.440 --> 27:05.600
The houses don't have any roofs and trees are growing inside them.

27:07.120 --> 27:14.320
The monkey people call this place their city and run around everywhere.

27:14.320 --> 27:19.600
Some monkeys play with the oranges and flowers in the King's Garden.

27:19.600 --> 27:22.800
And then they fight and shout.

27:22.800 --> 27:28.160
Others jump up and down and say silly things.

27:29.360 --> 27:34.080
The monkey people are happy because Mowgli is with them.

27:35.120 --> 27:38.880
This boy can teach us how to make things.

27:38.880 --> 27:40.960
Says one monkey.

27:40.960 --> 27:45.040
Yes, men make things with their hands.

27:45.040 --> 27:47.200
Says another monkey.

27:48.400 --> 27:51.760
But monkeys always forget the things they say.

27:52.880 --> 27:56.320
Mowgli is tired and hungry and says.

27:56.320 --> 27:59.440
Bring me some food.

28:01.200 --> 28:06.160
About 30 noisy monkeys go to get some fruit.

28:06.240 --> 28:10.400
About 30 noisy monkeys go to get some fruit.

28:11.200 --> 28:15.760
But they start fighting and forget to bring the fruit to Mowgli.

28:17.120 --> 28:20.800
Mowgli doesn't like the monkeys or the Lost City.

28:22.320 --> 28:25.040
Baloo's right, he thinks.

28:25.040 --> 28:27.600
The monkey people have no law.

28:28.560 --> 28:30.080
They are different from us.

28:30.720 --> 28:32.880
I must try to run away.

28:33.760 --> 28:37.520
Baloo and Beguira are probably angry with me.

28:39.360 --> 28:42.880
Mowgli tries to run to the walls of the Lost City.

28:43.680 --> 28:45.680
But the monkeys pull him back.

28:46.800 --> 28:48.720
You mustn't go away.

28:49.520 --> 28:50.240
They shout.

28:51.440 --> 28:53.520
You're happy here with us.

28:54.400 --> 28:55.600
We're great.

28:56.320 --> 28:57.680
We're wonderful.

28:58.480 --> 29:01.920
We all say this and it's true.

29:04.080 --> 29:06.720
Mowgli is tired and confused.

29:07.920 --> 29:10.000
When do these monkeys sleep?

29:10.560 --> 29:11.200
He thinks.

29:12.800 --> 29:17.680
He looks up at the sky and sees a big cloud near the moon.

29:19.120 --> 29:26.000
Perhaps that cloud is going to hide the moon and I can run away when it's dark.

29:27.840 --> 29:32.160
Beguira and Carr are also watching the same cloud.

29:32.960 --> 29:35.920
They are outside the walls of the Lost City.

29:37.440 --> 29:39.680
We must be careful.

29:40.320 --> 29:41.360
Says Beguira.

29:42.640 --> 29:47.760
There are only two of us and there are hundreds of monkeys.

29:49.200 --> 29:52.800
They are near the walls and they're talking to Mowgli.

29:53.760 --> 29:59.760
When the cloud hides the moon, I'm going to attack them.

30:00.720 --> 30:01.600
Good idea!

30:02.480 --> 30:03.440
Says Carr.

30:04.320 --> 30:12.400
I'm going to go up the hill and then I'm going to come down fast.

30:14.720 --> 30:20.240
Beguira enters the city walls silently and attacks the monkeys.

30:20.880 --> 30:24.320
He hits them with his strong black paws.

30:25.520 --> 30:28.080
The monkeys are scared and scream.

30:29.040 --> 30:30.800
But one of them shouts.

30:31.760 --> 30:33.600
Beguira is alone.

30:34.320 --> 30:36.240
Kill him! Kill him!

30:37.680 --> 30:44.240
Suddenly hundreds of monkeys jump on Beguira and hit, kick and bite him.

30:45.200 --> 30:48.560
Beguira fights bravely but he is alone.

30:49.520 --> 30:53.920
Other monkeys take Mowgli to an old broken building.

30:54.960 --> 30:59.520
They throw him into a dark room with one small window.

31:00.880 --> 31:06.720
Stay here with the poison people until we kill your friend Beguira.

31:07.600 --> 31:09.040
Says one monkey.

31:10.640 --> 31:12.080
Then we can play.

31:12.720 --> 31:18.640
In the dark room Mowgli can hear the hissing sounds of the poison people.

31:19.240 --> 31:22.000
This room is full of snakes.

31:22.000 --> 31:25.840
He thinks, I must give the snakes call.

31:26.560 --> 31:29.920
We are all one blood, you and I.

31:29.920 --> 31:33.920
He says giving the snakes call.

31:37.280 --> 31:39.440
The snakes answer.

31:39.440 --> 31:52.440
snake's answer. We're not going to bite you. But please don't don't move because your feet

31:52.440 --> 32:03.340
hurt us. All right, says Mowgli, listening to the noise of the fight outside. But Gira's

32:03.340 --> 32:12.640
fighting for his life. Thanks Mowgli. How can I help him? He remembers the big water fountain

32:12.640 --> 32:19.860
near the king's garden. He goes to the small window and shouts,

32:19.860 --> 32:28.200
but Gira go to the water fountain and jump into the water.

32:28.200 --> 32:41.360
But Gira hears him and thinks, oh good, Mowgli is safe. He slowly goes to the water fountain.

32:41.360 --> 32:46.360
Finally, Baloo arrives and shouts,

32:46.360 --> 33:00.360
Gira, I'm here. The monkeys jump on Baloo and he hits them with his big strong arms.

33:00.360 --> 33:10.360
Mowgli hears a loud splash when Baloo jumps into the water fountain. The monkeys are afraid

33:10.360 --> 33:15.360
of water and they stand around the fountain.

33:15.360 --> 33:22.360
Baloo cannot get out to help Baloo.

33:22.360 --> 33:26.360
Listening activity.

33:26.360 --> 33:37.360
Hello. I'd like some information about your jungle adventure tour to the lost city of Ascan.

33:37.360 --> 33:45.360
Oh yes, of course. There is a trip every week. The next trip leaves on the 10th of July.

33:45.360 --> 33:47.360
That's next Thursday.

33:47.360 --> 33:56.360
Good. We're here for another week. So that's perfect. At what time does the tour leave?

33:56.360 --> 34:05.360
It leaves at half past eight in the morning. The minibus leaves from the tourist information office.

34:05.360 --> 34:07.360
Do you know where that is?

34:07.360 --> 34:10.360
Yes. It's in the square.

34:10.360 --> 34:15.360
Yes. That's right. Do you want me to include you in the tour group?

34:15.360 --> 34:22.360
Yes. It's myself and three other people. So there are four of us.

34:22.360 --> 34:27.360
That's fine. I just need one name to make a reservation.

34:27.360 --> 34:33.360
You can have my name. It's Deborah Thompson.

34:33.360 --> 34:36.360
How do you spell that?

34:36.360 --> 35:02.360
Deborah is D, E, B, O, R, A, H. And Thompson is T, H, O, M, P, S, O, N.

35:02.360 --> 35:04.360
Thank you, Deborah.

35:04.360 --> 35:07.360
It's $20 each, right?

35:07.360 --> 35:17.360
Yes. That's right. The price is $20 per person and that includes the bus, lunch at the lost city and a tour guide.

35:17.360 --> 35:19.360
Thank you.

35:23.360 --> 35:29.360
Let's meet some of the animals in the story.

35:29.360 --> 35:31.360
Tigers.

35:31.360 --> 35:46.360
There are five kinds of tigers in the world. The Siberian, the Bengal, the Indo-Chinese, the South Chinese and the Sumatran.

35:46.360 --> 35:53.360
Tigers are big, strong animals and they live in Asia.

35:53.360 --> 36:01.360
They are carnivorous and they hunt alone at night because they have excellent night vision.

36:01.360 --> 36:05.360
They are also good swimmers.

36:05.360 --> 36:11.360
There are only about 7,000 tigers in the world today.

36:11.360 --> 36:16.360
They are in danger of extinction and this is very sad.

36:17.360 --> 36:24.360
People hunt them for their beautiful coats and this is against the law.

36:24.360 --> 36:29.360
Many countries are trying to save tigers.

36:30.360 --> 36:33.360
Bears.

36:33.360 --> 36:45.360
There are different kinds of bears in the world, the black bear, the grizzly, the Kodiak, the Alaskan brown bear

36:45.360 --> 36:48.360
and the polar bear.

36:48.360 --> 36:55.360
Bears are very big and heavy and have a lot of fur.

36:55.360 --> 36:59.360
They are strong, lively animals.

36:59.360 --> 37:06.360
They live in the forests and mountains of North America, Asia and Europe.

37:06.360 --> 37:12.360
But polar bears live in the Arctic Circle.

37:12.360 --> 37:22.360
They are carnivorous animals but they also like fish, fruit and honey.

37:22.360 --> 37:25.360
Indian Pythons.

37:25.360 --> 37:30.360
Indian Pythons are from the family of snakes.

37:30.360 --> 37:37.360
They are very big, long snakes and live in the jungles of India.

37:37.360 --> 37:41.360
They like living near water.

37:41.360 --> 37:45.360
They kill animals by squeezing them.

37:45.360 --> 37:51.360
They don't chew their food, they swallow their prey.

37:51.360 --> 37:57.360
Indian Pythons can even eat big animals like deer.

37:57.360 --> 38:03.360
After a big meal, they don't eat for days or weeks.

38:03.360 --> 38:08.360
Pythons are in danger of extinction too.

38:08.360 --> 38:17.360
People hunt them for their beautiful skin and use it to make bags, shoes and belts.

38:17.360 --> 38:23.360
In some countries, this is against the law.

38:23.360 --> 38:27.360
Black Panthers.

38:27.360 --> 38:31.360
Black Panthers are really black leopards.

38:31.360 --> 38:37.360
Their coat is very dark, so you cannot see its spots.

38:37.360 --> 38:42.360
Black Panthers live in Asia, Africa and the Far East.

38:42.360 --> 38:48.360
They are carnivorous and they live in forests and jungles.

38:48.360 --> 38:52.360
They like climbing up trees and sitting there.

38:52.360 --> 39:00.360
They are strong, clever animals and they hunt at night.

39:00.360 --> 39:02.360
Wolves.

39:02.360 --> 39:05.360
Wolves are social animals.

39:05.360 --> 39:09.360
They live and hunt together in a pack.

39:09.360 --> 39:15.360
Each pack has a leader and the other wolves must follow him.

39:15.360 --> 39:22.360
There are grey, brown, black, red and white wolves.

39:22.360 --> 39:26.360
They communicate with different sounds.

39:26.360 --> 39:32.360
They howl, bark and growl.

39:32.360 --> 39:41.360
Wolves live in the forests and mountains of Alaska, the United States, Northern Europe and Russia.

39:41.360 --> 39:45.360
They are in danger of extinction too.

39:45.360 --> 39:52.360
There are only about 150,000 wolves in the world today.

39:52.360 --> 39:57.360
Many of them live in national parks in the United States.

39:57.360 --> 40:05.360
Many countries have laws that protect wolves.

40:05.360 --> 40:11.360
6. Cars Dance.

40:11.360 --> 40:19.360
Suddenly, car comes down the hill fast and he is ready to attack the monkeys.

40:19.360 --> 40:27.360
They all know that car can kill any animal and they are afraid of him.

40:27.360 --> 40:31.360
When they see him, they shout.

40:31.360 --> 40:34.360
It's car! Run! Run!

40:34.360 --> 40:42.360
Then car opens his mouth and speaks one hissing word.

40:42.360 --> 40:51.360
The monkeys are suddenly quiet and everything in the lost city is silent.

40:51.360 --> 40:54.360
Beguira gets out of the fountain.

40:54.360 --> 40:58.360
Let's take Mowgli and go.

40:58.360 --> 41:00.360
He says.

41:00.360 --> 41:02.360
Thank you car.

41:02.360 --> 41:05.360
Yes. Thank you car.

41:05.360 --> 41:07.360
Says Baloo.

41:07.360 --> 41:09.360
You're great.

41:09.360 --> 41:14.360
Look at the monkeys. They're terrified.

41:14.360 --> 41:17.360
I'm happy to help.

41:17.360 --> 41:18.360
Says car.

41:18.360 --> 41:22.360
Where's the man cub?

41:22.360 --> 41:25.360
I'm here with the snakes.

41:25.360 --> 41:27.360
Cries Mowgli.

41:27.360 --> 41:29.360
I can't get out.

41:29.360 --> 41:32.360
Take him away.

41:32.360 --> 41:34.360
Shout the snakes.

41:34.360 --> 41:41.360
He jumps around and hurts us with his feet.

41:41.360 --> 41:48.360
The man cub has friends everywhere.

41:48.360 --> 41:50.360
Says car.

41:50.360 --> 41:57.360
He hits the wall with his heavy body three times and makes a hole in it.

41:57.360 --> 42:03.360
Mowgli jumps out and runs to Baloo and Beguira.

42:03.360 --> 42:05.360
Thank you for helping me.

42:05.360 --> 42:08.360
Says Mowgli, smiling.

42:08.360 --> 42:11.360
You must thank car.

42:11.360 --> 42:15.360
Say Baloo and Beguira.

42:15.360 --> 42:19.360
Mowgli looks at the great python.

42:19.360 --> 42:23.360
He looks a bit like a monkey.

42:23.360 --> 42:25.360
Says car.

42:25.360 --> 42:29.360
We're of one blood. You and I.

42:29.360 --> 42:31.360
Says Mowgli.

42:31.360 --> 42:36.360
I'm your friend and I can always help you.

42:36.360 --> 42:43.360
You're brave and you speak well.

42:43.360 --> 42:45.360
Says car.

42:45.360 --> 42:53.360
Now you must go with your friends.

42:53.360 --> 43:01.360
Car moves softly in front of the sitting monkeys and begins his dance.

43:01.360 --> 43:04.360
The hunger dance.

43:04.360 --> 43:09.360
His head moves slowly from right to left.

43:09.360 --> 43:16.360
His long body makes circles, squares and other shapes.

43:16.360 --> 43:21.360
He dances slowly and never stops.

43:21.360 --> 43:27.360
The monkeys are terrified, but they cannot move.

43:27.360 --> 43:33.360
Baloo and Beguira look at car and cannot move.

43:33.360 --> 43:38.360
Mowgli cannot understand what is happening.

43:38.360 --> 43:40.360
Monkeys!

43:40.360 --> 43:42.360
Cries car.

43:42.360 --> 43:45.360
Can you move?

43:45.360 --> 43:47.360
No car.

43:47.360 --> 43:49.360
They answer loudly.

43:49.360 --> 43:53.360
Without your word, we cannot move.

43:53.360 --> 43:59.360
Come close to me, monkeys.

43:59.360 --> 44:03.360
Says car in his low voice.

44:03.360 --> 44:08.360
Come very close.

44:08.360 --> 44:16.360
The monkeys move close to car and Baloo and Beguira move close too.

44:16.360 --> 44:22.360
Mowgli is worried and he pulls Baloo and Beguira away.

44:22.360 --> 44:25.360
Oh, thank you, Mowgli.

44:25.360 --> 44:28.360
Whisper's Beguira.

44:28.360 --> 44:30.360
What's happening?

44:30.360 --> 44:32.360
Asks Mowgli.

44:32.360 --> 44:35.360
Your eyes are closing.

44:35.360 --> 44:37.360
Are you feeling well?

44:37.360 --> 44:41.360
A python's dance is magic.

44:41.360 --> 44:44.360
Whisper's Beguira.

44:44.360 --> 44:48.360
It's very dangerous to watch, even for us.

44:48.360 --> 44:53.360
Because it's easy to walk into his mouth.

44:53.360 --> 44:54.360
Oh!

44:54.360 --> 44:57.360
Says Mowgli, surprised.

44:57.360 --> 45:01.360
The monkeys are moving close to car.

45:01.360 --> 45:10.360
Car is going to have a big dinner tonight with all of those monkeys.

45:10.360 --> 45:13.360
Whisper's Beguira.

45:13.360 --> 45:18.360
Let's go back to the jungle quickly.

45:18.360 --> 45:24.360
Baloo, Beguira and Mowgli leave the lost city.

45:24.360 --> 45:27.360
They go back to the jungle.

45:27.360 --> 45:30.360
And now, Mowgli?

45:30.360 --> 45:32.360
Says Beguira.

45:32.360 --> 45:35.360
We must follow the law of the jungle.

45:35.360 --> 45:40.360
We must punish you for talking to the monkeys.

45:40.360 --> 45:43.360
You're right, says Mowgli.

45:43.360 --> 45:46.360
I'm a bad man cub.

45:46.360 --> 45:50.360
He looks at Baloo sadly.

45:50.360 --> 45:55.360
We're sorry, but we cannot go against the law of the jungle.

45:55.360 --> 45:57.360
Says Baloo.

45:57.360 --> 46:00.360
You must learn, Mowgli.

46:00.360 --> 46:02.360
Says Beguira.

46:02.360 --> 46:08.360
Beguira hits him softly with his big paw six times.

46:08.360 --> 46:12.360
But Mowgli does not cry.

46:12.360 --> 46:15.360
You're a brave man cub.

46:15.360 --> 46:17.360
Says Baloo.

46:17.360 --> 46:20.360
Now, Beguira says,

46:20.360 --> 46:23.360
A jump on my back, little brother,

46:23.360 --> 46:28.360
and always remember to follow the law of the jungle.

46:28.360 --> 46:32.360
It's a good law and it keeps you safe.

46:32.360 --> 46:34.360
Let's go home.

46:34.360 --> 46:37.360
Yes, says Mowgli.

46:37.360 --> 46:40.360
I want to go home.

46:40.360 --> 46:48.360
He soon falls asleep on Beguira's back.

46:48.360 --> 46:53.360
Chapter 7, The Red Flower.

46:53.360 --> 47:01.360
All of the jungle people are Mowgli's friends, but not Sheer Khan.

47:01.360 --> 47:04.360
Beguira tells Mowgli.

47:04.360 --> 47:07.360
Be careful of Sheer Khan.

47:07.360 --> 47:09.360
He wants to kill you.

47:09.360 --> 47:13.360
A Kayla likes you, but he's old now.

47:13.360 --> 47:16.360
He's not strong.

47:16.360 --> 47:19.360
The young wolves don't listen to him.

47:19.360 --> 47:22.360
They listen to Sheer Khan.

47:22.360 --> 47:26.360
One day, you must kill him.

47:26.360 --> 47:29.360
I'm not afraid.

47:29.360 --> 47:31.360
Says Mowgli, laughing.

47:31.360 --> 47:34.360
I have you and Baloo.

47:34.360 --> 47:38.360
Mowgli, you must listen to me.

47:38.360 --> 47:41.360
Says Beguira softly.

47:41.360 --> 47:46.360
Remember, you're a man cub, not a wolf cub.

47:46.360 --> 47:50.360
You belong to the world of men.

47:50.360 --> 47:53.360
They're your brothers.

47:53.360 --> 47:57.360
One day, you must return to that world.

47:57.360 --> 48:02.360
You're clever, and you can do a lot of things we can't do.

48:02.360 --> 48:05.360
Because you're a man.

48:05.360 --> 48:07.360
Yes, Mowgli.

48:07.360 --> 48:09.360
Says Baloo.

48:09.360 --> 48:12.360
Sheer Khan's making trouble for you.

48:12.360 --> 48:16.360
The young wolves want to kill you.

48:16.360 --> 48:18.360
But why?

48:18.360 --> 48:20.360
Asks Mowgli.

48:20.360 --> 48:21.360
Look at me.

48:21.360 --> 48:24.360
Says Beguira.

48:24.360 --> 48:31.360
Mowgli looks him in the eyes, but Beguira turns his head away quickly.

48:31.360 --> 48:33.360
That's why.

48:33.360 --> 48:34.360
He says.

48:34.360 --> 48:36.360
You see, Mowgli.

48:36.360 --> 48:39.360
Even I can't look into your eyes.

48:39.360 --> 48:41.360
You're a man.

48:41.360 --> 48:43.360
You're clever.

48:43.360 --> 48:47.360
The young wolves know this, and they hate you.

48:47.360 --> 48:52.360
Mowgli listens to Beguira and Baloo quietly.

48:52.360 --> 48:58.360
You must go to the men's village and take some of their red flower.

48:58.360 --> 49:00.360
Says Beguira.

49:00.360 --> 49:04.360
All of the animals are afraid of it.

49:04.360 --> 49:10.360
It's a strong friend, and it can help you.

49:10.360 --> 49:17.360
The red flower is fire, but the animals do not call it by its name.

49:17.360 --> 49:21.360
Very well, says Mowgli.

49:21.360 --> 49:27.360
I'm going to the men's village to get the red flower now.

49:27.360 --> 49:35.360
In the village, he sees a young boy cover a fire pot with a cloth.

49:35.360 --> 49:42.360
Mowgli takes the pot from the boy and runs back to the jungle.

49:42.360 --> 49:49.360
That evening, the jackal, tobaccoe, goes to see Mowgli and says.

49:49.360 --> 49:55.360
There's a meeting at Council Rock tomorrow morning.

49:55.360 --> 50:03.360
When Mowgli gets to Council Rock, a tailor is not sitting on top of the big rock.

50:03.360 --> 50:07.360
He is sitting next to it.

50:07.360 --> 50:15.360
Sheer Khan is there too, and all of the young wolves are sitting around him.

50:16.360 --> 50:23.360
Mowgli sits next to Beguira with the fire pot between his legs.

50:23.360 --> 50:29.360
Sheer Khan starts speaking, and Mowgli jumps up.

50:29.360 --> 50:32.360
Is Sheer Khan your leader?

50:32.360 --> 50:34.360
asks Mowgli.

50:34.360 --> 50:38.360
Does he belong to the wolf pack?

50:38.360 --> 50:41.360
A tailor's old now.

50:41.360 --> 50:44.360
He's not important.

50:44.360 --> 50:46.360
Says Sheer Khan.

50:46.360 --> 50:49.360
Listen to me.

50:49.360 --> 50:54.360
A man cub doesn't belong to a wolf pack.

50:54.360 --> 50:57.360
Give him to me.

50:57.360 --> 50:59.360
A man!

50:59.360 --> 51:01.360
Cry the young wolves.

51:01.360 --> 51:06.360
A man doesn't belong to our wolf pack.

51:06.360 --> 51:12.360
A tailor is angry and says Mowgli is our brother.

51:12.360 --> 51:16.360
He respects the law of the jungle.

51:16.360 --> 51:20.360
Let him go away safely.

51:20.360 --> 51:22.360
But he's a man.

51:22.360 --> 51:27.360
Cry Sheer Khan and some of the wolves.

51:27.360 --> 51:31.360
Mowgli is very angry.

51:31.360 --> 51:35.360
He stands up with the fire pot in his hands.

51:35.360 --> 51:41.360
He takes a piece of wood and puts it in the fire.

51:41.360 --> 51:44.360
It starts burning.

51:44.360 --> 51:51.360
The wolves and the tiger are afraid of the fire and move away from Mowgli.

51:51.360 --> 51:54.360
You're the leader now.

51:54.360 --> 51:56.360
Says Beguira.

51:56.360 --> 51:59.360
Help your friend Akayla.

51:59.360 --> 52:02.360
I want to go to my people.

52:02.360 --> 52:04.360
Says Mowgli.

52:04.360 --> 52:11.360
But first he goes to Sheer Khan and says,

52:11.360 --> 52:17.360
You want to kill me, but now you're afraid of me.

52:17.360 --> 52:25.360
He hits Sheer Khan on the head with his burning stick and burns it a bit.

52:25.360 --> 52:28.360
The tiger is terrified.

52:28.360 --> 52:30.360
Go away now.

52:30.360 --> 52:32.360
Says Mowgli.

52:32.360 --> 52:43.360
But remember, I'm going to kill you one day and you must not kill my friend Akayla.

52:43.360 --> 52:48.360
He is free to live in the jungle.

52:48.360 --> 52:53.360
Mowgli jumps at the young wolves with his burning stick.

52:53.360 --> 52:59.360
They are terrified and run away with Sheer Khan.

52:59.360 --> 53:07.360
Only Akayla, Beguira and some old wolves stay at Council Rock.

53:07.360 --> 53:16.360
Suddenly, something inside Mowgli hurts and he starts crying.

53:16.360 --> 53:19.360
What's happening to me?

53:19.360 --> 53:21.360
He asks Beguira.

53:21.360 --> 53:24.360
Am I dying?

53:24.360 --> 53:29.360
You're a man and these are tears.

53:29.360 --> 53:32.360
Says Beguira.

53:32.360 --> 53:35.360
They're only tears.

53:35.360 --> 53:38.360
Now you must go to your people.

53:38.360 --> 53:44.360
You can't stay in the jungle anymore, my little brother.

53:44.360 --> 53:49.360
Yes, I must go to the world of men.

53:49.360 --> 53:51.360
Says Mowgli.

53:51.360 --> 53:57.360
But first, I want to say goodbye to my mother and father.

53:57.360 --> 54:05.360
He goes to the cave and cries on his mother's coat.

54:05.360 --> 54:08.360
Please don't forget me.

54:08.360 --> 54:10.360
Says Mowgli.

54:10.360 --> 54:12.360
Crying.

54:12.360 --> 54:16.360
Forget you, says Mother Wolf.

54:16.360 --> 54:18.360
Never.

54:18.360 --> 54:20.360
We love you.

54:20.360 --> 54:23.360
Come and visit us often.

54:23.360 --> 54:26.360
Says Father Wolf.

54:26.360 --> 54:29.360
Your mother and I are getting old.

54:29.360 --> 54:35.360
When I come to visit, I'm going to bring Sheer Khan's coat.

54:35.360 --> 54:38.360
Says Mowgli.

54:38.360 --> 54:48.360
The next morning, he goes down the hill to the world of men.

54:48.360 --> 54:50.360
Chapter 8.

54:50.360 --> 54:54.360
Tiger, Tiger.

54:54.360 --> 54:57.360
I have a lot of enemies now.

54:57.360 --> 54:59.360
Mowgli thinks.

54:59.360 --> 55:02.360
I must go far away.

55:02.360 --> 55:10.360
He runs and runs until he comes to a village near a lot of rocks and ravines.

55:10.360 --> 55:15.360
He sees cows and buffaloes everywhere.

55:15.360 --> 55:19.360
Some boys are looking after them.

55:19.360 --> 55:24.360
When they see Mowgli, they run away.

55:24.360 --> 55:28.360
Men here are afraid of the people of the jungle.

55:28.360 --> 55:31.360
thinks Mowgli.

55:31.360 --> 55:36.360
Mowgli sits near the village gate.

55:36.360 --> 55:43.360
When he sees a man, he opens his mouth to show that he wants some food.

55:43.360 --> 55:49.360
The man is surprised and runs to the village shouting.

55:49.360 --> 55:54.360
He comes back with about a hundred people.

55:54.360 --> 55:58.360
Everyone looks at Mowgli.

55:58.360 --> 55:59.360
Look.

55:59.360 --> 56:04.360
He has the bite marks of wolves on his arms and legs.

56:04.360 --> 56:06.360
Says one man.

56:06.360 --> 56:08.360
He's a wolf child.

56:08.360 --> 56:11.360
He comes from the jungle.

56:11.360 --> 56:14.360
These men don't understand.

56:14.360 --> 56:16.360
Think, Mowgli.

56:16.360 --> 56:19.360
I don't have bite marks.

56:19.360 --> 56:22.360
I have play marks.

56:22.360 --> 56:28.360
Wolf cubs always bite lightly when they play.

56:28.360 --> 56:31.360
He's a good looking boy.

56:31.360 --> 56:33.360
Says one woman.

56:33.360 --> 56:36.360
But he's thin.

56:36.360 --> 56:40.360
He must eat poor boy.

56:40.360 --> 56:44.360
Says Masua, another woman.

56:44.360 --> 56:48.360
He can come home with me.

56:48.360 --> 56:55.360
Masua takes Mowgli to her house and gives him some bread and milk.

56:55.360 --> 56:59.360
She is kind to him.

56:59.360 --> 57:05.360
This is my first time in a house and I don't like it.

57:05.360 --> 57:07.360
Think, Mowgli.

57:07.360 --> 57:13.360
But I'm a man now and I must do what men do.

57:13.360 --> 57:21.360
I know the languages of the jungle and now I must learn the language of men.

57:21.360 --> 57:27.360
That day, Mowgli learns a lot of words from Masua.

57:27.360 --> 57:33.360
But at night, he does not want to sleep inside a house.

57:33.360 --> 57:42.360
He climbs out of a small window and goes to sleep under a big tree near the village.

57:42.360 --> 57:47.360
He meets Grey Brother, a wolf cub.

57:47.360 --> 57:50.360
Hello little brother.

57:50.360 --> 57:52.360
Says Grey Brother.

57:52.360 --> 57:55.360
I have news for you.

57:55.360 --> 57:58.360
Shere Khan's in the mountains now.

57:58.360 --> 58:02.360
But he wants to kill you when he comes back.

58:03.360 --> 58:09.360
Please come to the big tree and tell me when Shere Khan comes back.

58:09.360 --> 58:11.360
Says Mowgli.

58:11.360 --> 58:13.360
Yes little brother.

58:13.360 --> 58:16.360
Says Grey Brother.

58:16.360 --> 58:20.360
And don't forget your wolf family.

58:20.360 --> 58:24.360
I can't forget the family I love.

58:24.360 --> 58:27.360
Says Mowgli smiling.

58:27.360 --> 58:32.360
For three months, Mowgli lives in the village.

58:32.360 --> 58:38.360
He learns to wear clothes, use money and work.

58:38.360 --> 58:43.360
Every day, he looks after cows and buffaloes.

58:43.360 --> 58:50.360
One day, Mowgli sees Grey Brother at the big tree.

58:50.360 --> 58:53.360
Shere Khan is back.

58:53.360 --> 58:55.360
Says Grey Brother.

58:55.360 --> 59:00.360
He wants to meet you outside the village gate tonight.

59:00.360 --> 59:04.360
But now he's hiding in the big ravine.

59:04.360 --> 59:06.360
Thank you, Grey Brother.

59:06.360 --> 59:08.360
Says Mowgli.

59:08.360 --> 59:11.360
He thinks for a moment.

59:11.360 --> 59:15.360
Then he looks at Grey Brother and says...

59:15.360 --> 59:17.360
The big ravine.

59:17.360 --> 59:24.360
I can take the buffaloes to the top and run after Shere Khan down the ravine.

59:24.360 --> 59:28.360
The cows can stay at the bottom of the ravine.

59:28.360 --> 59:33.360
In this way, he's between the buffaloes and the cows.

59:33.360 --> 59:36.360
And he can't run away.

59:36.360 --> 59:38.360
You're right.

59:38.360 --> 59:41.360
Says Grey Brother excitedly.

59:41.360 --> 59:43.360
Can you help me?

59:43.360 --> 59:45.360
Asks Mowgli.

59:45.360 --> 59:48.360
A tailor and I can help you.

59:48.360 --> 59:50.360
Says Grey Brother.

59:50.360 --> 59:53.360
And A tailor comes out from the trees.

59:53.360 --> 59:55.360
A tailor!

59:55.360 --> 59:57.360
Cries Mowgli happily.

59:57.360 --> 01:00:00.360
You're a true friend.

01:00:00.360 --> 01:00:05.360
Take the cows to the bottom of the ravine, Grey Brother.

01:00:05.360 --> 01:00:07.360
Says Mowgli.

01:00:07.360 --> 01:00:14.360
A tailor and I are going to take the buffaloes to the top.

01:00:14.360 --> 01:00:18.360
When Mowgli is ready, he shouts...

01:00:18.360 --> 01:00:20.360
Shere Khan!

01:00:20.360 --> 01:00:22.360
It's me!

01:00:22.360 --> 01:00:23.360
Mowgli!

01:00:23.360 --> 01:00:26.360
Are you ready?

01:00:26.360 --> 01:00:30.360
Mowgli gets on Rama, one of the buffaloes.

01:00:30.360 --> 01:00:35.360
And they all start running down the ravine.

01:00:35.360 --> 01:00:38.360
Shere Khan is sleeping.

01:00:38.360 --> 01:00:43.360
And he wakes up slowly when he hears the noise.

01:00:43.360 --> 01:00:46.360
The buffaloes are running towards him.

01:00:46.360 --> 01:00:52.360
He starts running down the ravine, but he is heavy with food.

01:00:52.360 --> 01:00:57.360
At the bottom of the ravine, he meets the cows.

01:00:57.360 --> 01:01:04.360
He falls under the feet of the buffaloes, and they run over him.

01:01:04.360 --> 01:01:11.360
Mowgli jumps off Rama's back, runs towards the tiger and shouts...

01:01:11.360 --> 01:01:13.360
Shere Khan's dead!

01:01:13.360 --> 01:01:15.360
He's dead!

01:01:16.360 --> 01:01:23.360
He takes his knife and starts cutting the coat from Shere Khan's body.

01:01:23.360 --> 01:01:26.360
It is hard work.

01:01:26.360 --> 01:01:33.360
The village hunter, Baldeo, sees Shere Khan's coat and thinks...

01:01:33.360 --> 01:01:37.360
I want that tiger coat.

01:01:37.360 --> 01:01:40.360
He goes to talk to Mowgli.

01:01:40.360 --> 01:01:44.360
Go, and look after your cows.

01:01:44.360 --> 01:01:46.360
He says...

01:01:46.360 --> 01:01:49.360
The tiger coat is mine.

01:01:49.360 --> 01:01:51.360
I'm the village hunter.

01:01:51.360 --> 01:01:55.360
I can sell it for a lot of money.

01:01:55.360 --> 01:01:56.360
No!

01:01:56.360 --> 01:01:58.360
Cries Mowgli.

01:01:58.360 --> 01:02:01.360
Don't touch this coat!

01:02:01.360 --> 01:02:02.360
Listen, boy!

01:02:02.360 --> 01:02:04.360
Says Baldeo.

01:02:04.360 --> 01:02:13.360
Suddenly, a cayler jumps on him, and he is on the ground with a big grey wolf on top of him.

01:02:13.360 --> 01:02:17.360
Now, go back to the village, Baldeo.

01:02:17.360 --> 01:02:21.360
Says Mowgli.

01:02:21.360 --> 01:02:25.360
Baldeo is afraid and goes away.

01:02:25.360 --> 01:02:32.360
That evening, Mowgli goes back to the village and sees the people at the gate.

01:02:32.360 --> 01:02:34.360
Go away, wolf child!

01:02:34.360 --> 01:02:36.360
Jungle boy!

01:02:36.360 --> 01:02:38.360
They shout...

01:02:38.360 --> 01:02:41.360
We don't want you here!

01:02:41.360 --> 01:02:45.360
They start throwing stones at him.

01:02:45.360 --> 01:02:48.360
Mowgli doesn't understand.

01:02:48.360 --> 01:02:53.360
Shere Khan kills their cows and takes their children.

01:02:53.360 --> 01:02:55.360
He thinks...

01:02:55.360 --> 01:02:59.360
But the people of the village are angry with me.

01:02:59.360 --> 01:03:04.360
They're like the bad young wolves of the pack.

01:03:04.360 --> 01:03:09.360
He looks at the stars in the night sky and says...

01:03:10.360 --> 01:03:15.360
I don't want to sleep in houses anymore.

01:03:15.360 --> 01:03:18.360
He turns to a cayler and says...

01:03:18.360 --> 01:03:23.360
Let's take Shere Khan's coat and go away.

01:03:23.360 --> 01:03:29.360
Mowgli and the two wolves go to Mother Wolf's cave.

01:03:29.360 --> 01:03:33.360
The people of the village don't want me, Mother.

01:03:33.360 --> 01:03:35.360
Says Mowgli.

01:03:35.360 --> 01:03:37.360
This is my home.

01:03:37.360 --> 01:03:40.360
I want to stay here.

01:03:40.360 --> 01:03:45.360
And this is Shere Khan's coat.

01:03:45.360 --> 01:03:48.360
Mother Wolf is very happy.

01:03:48.360 --> 01:03:52.360
Beguira comes to the cave and says...

01:03:52.360 --> 01:03:57.360
We're happy to see you, little brother.

01:03:57.360 --> 01:04:03.360
Mowgli takes Shere Khan's coat and puts it on council rock.

01:04:03.360 --> 01:04:07.360
A cayler sits on it and says...

01:04:07.360 --> 01:04:11.360
Look carefully, wolves.

01:04:11.360 --> 01:04:15.360
Shere Khan is dead.

01:04:15.360 --> 01:04:20.360
Now I don't belong to the wolf pack or to the man pack.

01:04:20.360 --> 01:04:22.360
Says Mowgli.

01:04:22.360 --> 01:04:26.360
But I can hunt alone in the jungle.

01:04:26.360 --> 01:04:29.360
We can hunt with you.

01:04:29.360 --> 01:04:33.360
Say, grey brother and the other cubs.

01:04:33.360 --> 01:04:42.360
Mowgli returns to the jungle and lives and hunts with his brothers.

